The Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) has decided to retain its key interest rate by 14 percent to stimulate the economy. Eight members of the committee voted to retain the policy rate, said Godwin Emefiele, CBN governor. The MPC also kept the assymmetric corridor at +200 and -500 basis points.  According to the CBN Governor, “non performing loans are satisfactorily being addressed by banks and as Nigeria pays off its huge contractual debts, the NPL ratio will also come down”.  Details later…